==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Precursor
<hw>Pre*cur"sor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praecursor</ets>, fr. <ets>praecurrere</ets> to run before;
<ets>prae</ets> before + <ets>currere</ets> to run. See
<er>Course</er>.]</ety> <def>One who, or that which, precedes an event,
and indicates its approach; a forerunner; a harbinger.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Evil thoughts are the invisible, airy <qex>precursors</qex> of all
the storms and tempests of the soul.</q>
<rj><qau>Buckminster.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Predecessor; forerunner; harbinger; messenger;
omen; sign.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Precursorship</ent>⟦br⟧
